<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-02-02T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-02-02T15:00:00-05:00" n="184" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d184">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/2848: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-02-02T15:00:00-05:00">February 2, 1933—3
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>12. As soon as Cruchaga returns from Mendoza endeavor discreetly to find
                            out result of his conversation with Argentine Minister of Foreign
                            Affairs especially as regards the Chaco.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>